{
  "texts": [
    "ReasoningThe NLP community typically assesses LLMs based on different types of reasoning skills, such as arithmetic reasoning, commonsense reasoning, logical reasoning, symbolic reasoning, and multimodal reasoning.",
    "This section focuses on forms of reasoning that require familiarity with real-world knowledge and excludes mathematical and logical reasoning, which will be covered in the following sections.",
    "It should be noted that there is some overlap between these concepts.Critical thinking, decision making, and problem solving are all crucial activities that rely heavily on the fundamental aspect of human intelligence known as reasoning.",
    "Models like ChatGPT lack a \"world model\", Spatial reasoning refers to the ability to understand and manipulate the relationships between objects, people, and places in the physical space around us.",
    "It involves visualizing and mentally transforming objects in 2D or 3D space and recognizing patterns, transformations, and relationships between objects."
  ]
}